<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="775" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d775">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51 Relief Credits/148</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-27"><hi rend="italic">July 27,
                                1928</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received August 9.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1798</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s confidential
                            instruction No. 1017 of June 21st last regarding the proposed new
                            reconstruction loan to Austria,<note n="58" xml:id="d775fn58">Not
                                printed; see similar instruction to Minister in Austria, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> I have the honor to report that
                            in the course of a conversation at the Foreign Office to-day with
                            Undersecretary Grandi, he informed me that there had been no change in
                            the Italian Government’s attitude with regard to this matter, as
                            expressed to the Department by the Italian Ambassador.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Henry P.
                            Fletcher</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>